## 6. Shared Base Components

### `BpmnResizableNode.tsx` — The Universal Wrapper

ALL node components (except `BpmnLaneNode` and `BpmnDataNode`) wrap their content in `<BpmnResizableNode>`. It:
- Renders a `<NodeResizer>` (only visible when `selected === true`) with resize handles
- Renders a `<NodeResizeControl position="bottom-right">` (hidden when not selected)
- Handle style: 8×8px, border `hsl(var(--border))`, bg `hsl(var(--card))`, borderRadius 2

```tsx
// BpmnResizableNode — key props:
type Props = {
  selected: boolean;
  minWidth: number;
  minHeight: number;
  maxWidth?: number;
  maxHeight?: number;
  keepAspectRatio?: boolean;
  onResize?: ...
  onResizeEnd?: ...
  children: ReactNode;
};
```

### `helpers.tsx` — Shared Styling & Utilities

**`getBpmnNodeClassName(kind, selected)`** — the key selection styling function:

```ts
const base = 'relative text-foreground transition-colors';
const focus = selected ? 'ring-2 ring-ring/40' : 'ring-0';

// Per-kind classes:
task:                  'border border-border bg-card'
subprocess:            'border border-border bg-card'
event-start:           'rounded-full border-2 border-emerald-600 bg-card'
event-intermediate:    'rounded-full border-2 border-amber-500 bg-card'
event-end:             'rounded-full border-[3px] border-red-600 bg-card'
gateway:               'border border-slate-500 bg-card'
data-object:           'bg-card'
data-store:            'bg-card'
annotation:            'border border-border bg-card'
group:                 'border border-dashed border-border bg-muted/10'
pool:                  'border-2 border-border bg-muted/20'
lane:                  'border border-dashed border-border bg-muted/25'
```

**Default node sizes** (from `getBpmnNodeSize`):
| Kind | Width | Height |
|---|---|---|
| task | 160 | 72 |
| subprocess | 220 | 96 |
| event-start/intermediate/end | 56 | 56 |
| gateway | 72 | 72 |
| data-object | 96 | 120 |
| data-store | 120 | 90 |
| annotation | 120 | 60 |
| group | 240 | 160 |
| pool | 720 | 240 |
| lane | 720 | 100 |

**`BpmnNodeHandles`** — renders `@xyflow/react` `<Handle>` components. All handles styled: `h-2 w-2 border border-border bg-card`. Props: `left`, `right` (default true), `top`, `bottom` (default false).

**`BpmnNodeLabel`** — renders: `<p className="select-none text-xs text-foreground ...">`.

**`getNodeLabel(data, fallback)`** — reads `data.label` string, falls back to provided string.

---

## Summary: How Selection Styling Works

1. **`ring-2 ring-ring/40`** is applied via `getBpmnNodeClassName(kind, selected)` to the inner `div` when `selected === true`. This is the primary "selected" indicator — a semi-transparent ring.
2. **`BpmnResizableNode`** additionally shows `<NodeResizer>` (react-flow's built-in resize overlay) and the `bottom-right` resize control handle when selected.
3. Event nodes (`EventShell`) do NOT use `getBpmnNodeClassName` — they don't get the `ring-*` class. Their selection is only indicated by the `<NodeResizer>` appearing.
4. `BpmnLaneNode` does NOT use `BpmnResizableNode` — it has no resize controls and uses `getBpmnNodeClassName('lane', selected)` but only within a plain `div`.

**The selection ring CSS:** `ring-2 ring-ring/40` — Tailwind's `ring` utility using the `--ring` CSS variable at 40% opacity. This is the ONLY selected-state visual diff for most nodes.

